race.comment: Competitive contest to kick off the card. POCKETMONEY (5) has a handy record around this circuit, winning two of three starts and has been racing consistently of late. Moor sticks in the irons following that last-start placing and should be right there when the whips are cracking. KEIKO SAY (8) has a win and a placing from two attempts over this seven-furlong journey and gets in well at the weights with the claim. Looms as the main danger. KINROSS LANE (4) has hit the top-five in all eight career outings and doesn't know how to put in a poor one. A must for the multiples. PRIDE OF VENUS (9) has hit a purple patch up north and has earned her shot at this company now. Hard to knock mares in form. LUTON HOO (2) is a last-start winner who shouldn't be slept on.
